<table width=100%>
<tr>
<td width=50%><font color=white>Posted By: Snark</font></td><td width=50% align=right><font color=white>2000-08-08 12:08:53</font></td></tr><tr>
<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>Xalgoz is a 40 minute spawn at the bottom of Kaesora, with a potential placeholder.  In the 15 or so times I waited for him to pop, he popped about 10 times.  The other times a regular skeleton showed.  He has no "common" drop, but more often than not he seems to drop the Sword of Xalgoz.  If you're lucky he'll drop the Fang of Xalgoz which is required for the key to Charasis quest (and why most people camp him).  RARELY he drops the Staff of the Dreaded Gaze.<BR>
<BR>
The Staff is OK, but not great... the prime reason being that the Invoke Fear effect takes THREE times longer to cast (ie: 7.5 seconds).  Yes, I save 120 mana per shot, but when I fear kite I have everything shaved to a fine margin and those extra 5 seconds to get a Fear off after it breaks sometimes results in it getting interrupted.  Furthermore, it IS a 2 hander which means you'll be giving up everything except for 100 mana at level 50 to wield this staff.  With the Dread Widow thxyl being very similar to the Glowing Black Stone, but way more available, you'll ask yourself why you're holding this staff.  So, keep the staff for soloing (if you can get used to it) and keep your two 1h items in your inventory for dungeons and raids.  Then switch accordingly.<BR>
<BR>
NOTE:  You MUST have the staff equipped to use the Fear effect!<BR>
<BR>
One last thing:  people die ALL THE TIME in Kaesora and moan about losing their corpse.  Do NOT become a statistic who ends up venting their frustration of one-way dungeons on the public forums.  If you don't know what you're doing, group with a Necro who has Summon Corpse.  <BR>
<BR>
<BR>
</font></td></tr></table>
<BR>
<table width=100%>
<tr>
<td width=50%><font color=white>Posted By: Erinin</font></td><td width=50% align=right><font color=white>2000-09-06 22:53:48</font></td></tr><tr>
<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>Although the casting time on this item is long, it is a VERY nice tool to use when soloing in outdoor zones.  The trick is to figure out the aproximate time that fear usually breaks (about 42 seconds) and start casting it before it does.  Keep in mind that this doesn't always work, but it's a great item nontheless, and saves a lot of mana from fears.  BTW, this item is a TERRIBLY long camp, people go for weeks without seeing one drop</font></td></tr></table>
<BR>
<table width=100%>
<tr>
<td width=50%><font color=white>Posted By: Nefarien</font></td><td width=50% align=right><font color=white>2000-09-17 07:58:03</font></td></tr><tr>
<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>From what i have experienced, this might be one of the rarest drops in the game.  A person I recently spoke to said that her guild had camped the guy for over 100 spawns for Famgs and had never seen one.  I was lucky enough to acquire one from a guildmate in exchange for a Stave of Shielding...I kid you not, i CANNOT enter a populated zone without at least 3 or 4 /tells about what/where this thing is.  For those that have not seen it, it appears as one of the see-through crystal-type staves ( like the popular Monk staff) with a sarnak skull on it.  The stats are not tremendous and the Invoke Fear effect IS very slow as someone pointed out, but if you are interested in having a unique look, this is the staff to have.<BR>
<BR>
</font></td></tr></table>
