<table width=100%>
<tr>
<td width=50%><font color=white>Posted By: Deadly</font></td><td width=50% align=right><font color=white>2000-11-17 18:25:05</font></td></tr><tr>
<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>I too have been offered obscene amounts of trades or cash for my staff and I will tell you that I was tempted when seveal nice items were displayed in a trade window.    But I will not get rid of it.     I cast fear twice (at least) per battle, so that is 200 mana.   So that makes the staff +6 int +240 mana  no item comes close.    And that 200 mana you do not have to med back, it is always there.   By far the most usefull and impressive items in the game.    Jaundice bone bracer is nice also, need to get my shaman one of those (also mana free)<BR>
<BR>
One last thing.... while you are running you can keep pressing the staff effect and you look like a bard running around.    You have swirling green skulls and glowing red sparkles coming off you like a fireball.    Very impressive look... you will get many shouts in the zone on how your doing that.       </font></td></tr></table>
